{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 417553, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Psychoshamoo", "body": "This is doable with only 1 onyxia cloak, which will be on the tank. If you stand DIRECTLY IN THE CENTER BEHIND THE THRONE, the raid will not be affected by shadow flame. Positioning should be set as soon as the /yell during phase 1. I have done this every BWL clear since 3.0 and it works every time.", "date": "2008-10-23T13:17:53-05:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Confirmed that this still works.  Our tank actually did not have a cloak, but had a huge amount of HP.  After the initial wave I (pally) bubbled out and healed him (the bubble was just precautionary), I was able to keep him up w/ enough heals and his HP was high enough to live long enough for the DoT to tick off.  So it is possible to do this with ZERO people having the cloak as long as the tank and healer is decently geared for 80.  It's a good idea to have another tank or two on standby incase the \"sacrifical\" tank dies to pick up nef (this also happened since we forgot nefarion fears :p)", "creationdate": "2008-12-31T01:47:52-06:00", "id": 68986, "rating": 8, "commentid": 417553, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "sentinelk9", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
