{"commentv2": 1, "number": 30, "id": 1013165, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "malcore1nathan", "body": "Onyxia's brother, and deathwings son.\r\nIt would be REALLY awesome if they made blackwing lair a raid for lv 85, without attunments, for next patch, becuese when lv 60 was out, he was sopposed to be bigger, harder, stronger, and a LOT harder to reach becuese u had to go thru 7 bosses to get to him,and only 5 adds to get to onyxia.", "date": "2010-04-05T13:04:32-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 31, "id": 1129369, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "DrCheis", "body": "I didn't do BWL in the old days, but recently when I started running it on my Druid, I found the druid class call seemed... deficient.\r\n\r\nI was placed into cat form, but still able to cancel the form manually and shift into moonkin. Maybe it's a bug from starting in moonkin? Also, odly when hit with the \"cat form lock\" I was still able to cast my regular spells even though my model appeared as a cat. It seems to be only a cosmetic debuff now, I'm guessing a bug.\r\n\r\nI felt guilty though and meleed in cat form anyway until it wore off.", "date": "2010-09-27T15:59:10-05:00", "rating": 25, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Back in vanilla, when you were forced into cat form, you were unable to shift out of it. Since vanilla raiding druids were mostly healers, the class call basically removed a portion of your healer force. I presume due to the numerous patches blizzard has added to the game, somewhere along the way the call got broken and blizzard never bothered fixing it again.", "creationdate": "2010-10-03T09:42:51-05:00", "id": 184866, "rating": 20, "commentid": 1129369, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "LeminaAusa", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 32, "id": 1148981, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "nobleknight", "body": "There's a Death Knight Call now, but I couldn't figure out exactly what it did. He yelled, \"Death Knights...get over here!\", but I didn't see the effect it had on the DK in my party (Nefarian's huge foot was kind of in my way) - what does he do?", "date": "2010-10-21T02:20:51-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Read the comments, it Death Grips the whole raid, pulling all players in the raid to melee range", "creationdate": "2010-10-21T05:49:05-05:00", "id": 187839, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1148981, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "387878", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 33, "id": 1152269, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "224327", "body": "I am beginning to wonder if he is bugged ever since the 4.0.1 patch.\r\n\r\nGranted the block changes really took a toll on my soloing ability, it seems to me that his add spawning is borked.  Pre-patch I used to simply tank them all with no issues, but now there are so many adds on my screen that it begins to freeze the game (where as before this didn't happen).\r\n\r\nHas anyone been regularly killing him as well and could weigh in on this?", "date": "2010-10-24T17:22:44-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yes it happends everytime.. It wasnt like that for me much in Cataclysm though. It came in 4.3.4. Atleast for me", "creationdate": "2013-09-04T10:00:03-05:00", "id": 689520, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1152269, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Tyerr", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 34, "id": 1157327, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Vaugn", "body": "The priests' call is definitely borked as of 4.0.1.  Consider this line from my combat log:\n\nVaugn suffers 8543 Shadow damage from Vaugn's Corrupted Healing. (2707 Resisted) (2158 Overkill).  That's a whopping 13,000+ damage in one tick.  I had glanced at my screen a few moments before I died and I had just 1 stack on me.\n\nThe mage I am with has noticed ridiculous corrupted healing amounts for him as well.  Egads!\n\nFurther testing has found that smite + atonement as well as glyphed power word: shield will not cause corrupted healing.  (Not sure about prayer of mending, so I've been avoiding it).\n\nI am duo'ing Nef with a mage.  It's actually a major pain, since I'm either being semi-chain polymorphed, or I can't cast direct heals.  And Nef does a lot of damage during that half a minute or so that I'm polymorphed.  Once the mage died though I find that I can handle him quite nicely on my own so long as I avoid the corrupted healing debuff (since even a single stack = death within moments).\n\nEdit: Learned a bit more info so I added it above.", "date": "2010-10-31T02:57:11-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-10-31T03:39:37-05:00", 1, "Vaugn"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 35, "id": 1158033, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Leppy", "body": "Just downed this guy with a dk specced dps, a mage, and 2 resto druids. (level 80 and none of us too well geared.)\r\n\r\nOur group wiped aside from one druid when nef summoned all of his minions at around 300k hp. That druid b-rezzed a healing druid in full resto gear, then died. Leaving the resto to fight this guy from 260k hp to zero. \r\n\r\nNef kept the druid feared and in cat form most of the fight, but they were able to heal via rejuv and such when the buff wore off. A 3-7  second window of healing after it wears off, so you're probably better off NOT having druid healers unless your tanks are great or well geared.\r\n\r\nWe got the fight done though <3 and I know who to call for a pug.", "date": "2010-10-31T23:26:29-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 36, "id": 1163516, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Cithiel", "body": "Just a nice tip for warlocks, when he summons all the adds back at 20% use soulburn + seed of corruption. Placing corruption on all the adds (completely avoiding the AoE damage restrictions) and if you're affliction specced, giving you insane healing.\r\n\r\nWe two manned him as affliction warlock and feral druid, we had some trouble in phase 1 where the MC nearly got the druid killed. We also had some initial trouble at 20%, but SoC + soulburn made it into a cakewalk. 100+ gold from loot, yes please!", "date": "2010-11-06T10:54:50-05:00", "rating": 16, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
