{"commentv2": 1, "number": 66, "id": 2132854, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Mystterious", "body": "Man! it seems everyone knows how to kill him but nobody tells you how to solo him now in the latest patch, when we are IL 670 or something near that IL. I'm frost mage IL 670. To me all the comments here are like hey: \"I KNOW HOW TO KILL HIM, and NOT YOU HAHAHAHAHAHAHA\". Anyone could explain how to kill him? I woul like to know it from someone who can solo it ALONE!\n\nI tell you whazzup atm: I'm in front of Onyxia, Onyxia is in the bottom of the square on the lowest floor, I'm on the second floor,Onyxia is too far, I cant cast something at her. And Nefarian fly in circle over me. \n\nLast time I jumped down to go kill Onyxia, I killed Onyxia fairly rapidly, yes! But 1 sec after, lava tides appeared! I managed to reach one of the three trays, to be out of the lava, but the lava has reduced my life to 5%.\n\nWhen I was on one of the three trays, outside the lava, Nefarian and a really big bunch of mobs killed me because my life was at 5%)\n\n[small]Facultative note: I used a potion, I was on the effect of a flask, Now I will add a Focus  Augment Rune to theses items.\n[/small]\n\nI'll retry now, I'm in the second floor and I'll jump down again :)\nIt's cool, I can try to learn the strats by myself BUT\nYOU CAN HELP ME! Who me? YES YOU!\n\nIf you read this you see a man in trouble, I've search  here and I have not found an answer!\nI've watched the comments section of nefarian and the comments section of onyxia.\n\nNo matter the reason why you click downvote, it's going to hurt me if you downvote.\n\nIf you want to help me, Vote up for this comment, this comment is helpful, and type a message that explain how to kill that boss, anything that might be helpful. If you don't know how to kill that boss, just up vote this comment, it will help me too because this comment will stay if people vote for it, and maybe one day, we will have a comment that explain how to kill it right here with a lot of votes!\n\nI go die, I mean try, again!\n\nThank you very much\nGood game, good luck, have fun!\nMystterious\n\n~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\n\nOK I KILLED IT ON THE SECOND ATTEMP! It was easy finally!\n\nFollow theses steps:\n\n1. Go kill Onyxia ASAP. For that, use all your cooldowns, your flasks your runes, your buffs, your feast, EVERYTHING.\n2. After Onyxia is dead, reach 1 of the 3 trays, because when the lava tides will appear, you will have to swim in the lava to jump on the trays of your choice.\n3. Kill the npc on the trays\n4. Cast everything at Nefarian. You can jumpdown when the lava tides dissapear. For the melee, I suppose ou will have to wait til the lava tides dissapear and Nefarian lands on the ground. Then you will be able to KUNG-FU him!\n\nHope this help a lot\n\nFeel free to add some useful comments, for melee people or for anything else.\n\nGood game, good luck, have fun!\nMystterious", "date": "2015-03-07T20:34:50-06:00", "rating": -7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This page here is for the Level-60-Version of Nefarian in Blackwing Lair, while the original comment seems to refer to [URL=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=41376/nefarian] his Level-85-Version. For additional Information and tatics how to beat him there follow the link.", "creationdate": "2015-03-21T11:40:32-05:00", "id": 856660, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2132854, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Sentro", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2015-03-07T21:24:39-06:00", 9, "Mystterious"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 67, "id": 2140283, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "blabblez", "body": "Just a quick note if you are trying to grind a lowbie an item. I was trying to run my twink through here and he would die every time. Dancing around the pillars wasn't working. So I put him in one of the spawning caves. Tucked him in the corner of the door and he was always getting hit, then I took my 100 in there as well and aoe'd everything until nefarian went into dragon form. was able to go out of the cave and kill after that. Every other attempt my lowbie died and the thing was reset. but this way I avoided the mc using los and worked flawlessly.", "date": "2015-03-19T05:59:42-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 68, "id": 2316399, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Almachai", "body": "Running Blackwing Lair has become a routine for me because it is one of the vanilla dungeons/raids left untouched by Cataclysm level scaling and subsequent item removal.\n\nBlackwing Lair is the only way to get most dragonscales anymore, especially [item=15416], which some choose to make some nice transmog items with. This scarcity of scales is because Upper Blackrock Spire's black dragons were removed, and most remaining dragons in Azeroth have had their levels altered so that they no can longer drop scales adequately.\n\nThe pets in this raid are also good for collecting, pet battles, and selling.\n\nLastly, Nefarian drops some incredible recipes, and not too uncommonly either. I have had a huge variety of these loot-list items drop, and they are even more difficult to come by in the world anymore because of aforementioned level scaling. He can also drop [item=1973], which have upped in value since they became a toy.\n\nHere is a list of recipes he has personally dropped [i][b]at least[/b][/i] once for me:\n\n[ul]\n[li][item=12720][/li]\n[li][item=14510][/li]\n[li][item=14497][/li]\n[li][item=14507][/li]\n[li][item=14501][/li]\n[li][item=12716]*** from mobs in BWL[/li]\n[li][item=7976]*** This is arguably the least valuable, most common plan Nefarian drops[/li]\n[li][item=8028][/li]\n[li][item=11226][/li]\n[li][item=12692][/li]\n[li][item=13518]*** A guildie friend found this from him[/li]\n[li][item=13488][/li]\n[li][item=13487][/li]\n[li][item=16055][/li]\n[li][item=16044][/li]\n[li][item=15742][/li]\n[/ul] \n\n[s]The biggest issue I've seen people have is getting past the first boss. It definitely is a strategy one needs to get accustomed to. Here are my tips for soloing:\n\n1.) Grab the orb to start, take out all the eggs and make your way slowly to your character\n2.) When you get a dragonkin on you, lull it to sleep with spell \"5\"\n3.) Let go of the boss with escape or the red arrow and AoE the mobs around you. And depending on your character, throw a HoT on yourself. That will help aggro stay on you\n4.) Don't let go of Razorgore near the end. The aggro shift won't do much after you've gotten to a certain point\n5.) [b]DO NOT[/b] attack him until he heals himself. If you do, he will reset and kill everybody.[/s]\n\n[i]EDIT: Razorgore has been made pretty much wipe proof. His egg destroy spell no longer has a cooldown. Just wait about 2 seconds before killing him after all the eggs are destroyed.\n[/i]\nI hope this helps. Good luck farming!", "date": "2016-03-23T16:26:29-05:00", "rating": 17, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "the full list of what he drops isn't on his wowhead page and he's only listed on the recipe pages as an npc a recipe can drop from. if you don't know what recipes he drops, you can't look it up! to add to this list, the following dropped from him for me: [url=https://www.wowhead.com/item=14511/pattern-gloves-of-spell-mastery#dropped-by:0+3-10-9+1]Pattern: Gloves of Spell Mastery[/url] (he's not even listed as an npc who drops this recipe) and [url=https://www.wowhead.com/item=14509/pattern-mooncloth-circlet]Pattern: Mooncloth Circlet[/url]. Anyone else have any drop to add to this list?", "creationdate": "2017-10-12T07:29:26-05:00", "id": 1079404, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2316399, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "kitkat2", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just use the Database Item Search here, go to: Database > Items > Recipes, then set filter \"Drops in... (Zone): Blackwing Lair\". All recipes listed can drop from Nefarian, except the \"Goblin's Guide to Elementium\".", "creationdate": "2017-10-28T14:33:08-05:00", "id": 1081970, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2316399, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "rzzbr", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Black Dragonscales drop from Onyxia as well", "creationdate": "2019-01-18T05:21:07-06:00", "id": 1216060, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2316399, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Monomatapa", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2018-01-14T12:33:53-06:00", 1, "Almachai"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 69, "id": 2359926, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "TevishSzat", "body": "I won't lie, this guy is a big part of the reason why I'd like to see Timewalking LFR (the other biggest part is Kara).  He keeps getting new class calls every time one gets added to the game, but will never really face a Demon Hunter in a 'fair' fight, for instance.  He's one of the coolest fights that most people will never get a chance to experience as a challenge... unless of course folks get scaled down to his level.  I suppose the phase transition that once was an instant kill without the right gear would have to be nerfed, but other than that his fight would be as interesting and hectic as it ought to be.", "date": "2016-08-01T08:54:57-05:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "They would have to first 'fix' hunter call. Because while original one was brutal, right now they are only class that effectively has no call, despite all new classes getting one.", "creationdate": "2016-11-04T11:28:24-05:00", "id": 1005250, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2359926, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Casn", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Maybe they could have one where a Freeze Trap appears underneath them and triggers. \"Hunter, always relying on your traps. Do you not think perhaps you'll step into one yourself?\"", "creationdate": "2018-05-08T18:27:22-05:00", "id": 1111589, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2359926, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "StealthTheFox", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
