{"commentv2": 1, "number": 10, "id": 1298568, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "317684", "body": "During the phase 2 > 3 transition, Nef will cast [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=79353]Shadow of Cowardice[/url] on anyone who is still standing on the pillar when he lands ... so make sure you jump down when you are supposed to so you don't get 1 shotted.", "date": "2011-01-18T01:25:40-06:00", "rating": 28, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 1305149, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "76689", "body": "In order to fight the raid wide aoe [spell=81272], I find [item=62471] seems be a lifesaver, an additional 25% resistance cuts off incoming lightning damage is enormous, this is especially critical for the off tank who is on add duty that often times get zapped and one-shotted by the skeletons. My question is this. Since it's on a 1-min cd, the raid could theoretically time its use every 10% when the lighting strikes. I wonder has anyone ever tried it, and perhaps recommend it for the whole raid to purchase it? I'm considering to demand my guild to equip it for progressions and maybe future heroic mode encounters. Some actual usage comment would be appreciated.", "date": "2011-01-23T01:27:09-06:00", "rating": 15, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "If that's what is messing you up, then yea, definitely. On the other hand, Uunequipping a DPS trinket would cost a DPS ~2-5% of their overall damage, depending on how good mastery is for each class and how good the trinket they're replacing is. You might take more overall damage by downing the boss slower.  As far as the off-tank having one, he definitely should. That's the best tank trinket in any fight with burst magic damage.", "creationdate": "2011-01-24T19:39:37-06:00", "id": 218561, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1305149, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "632461", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Good tip for rogues, use feint. Healers will love you.", "creationdate": "2011-02-15T14:59:52-06:00", "id": 225380, "rating": 16, "commentid": 1305149, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Baremyteeth", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 1318114, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "448060", "body": "I need a timer for [url=http://www.wowhead.com/search?q=shadowblaze#spells]Shadowblaze[/url]. DBM is announcing Shadowblaze [i]after[/i] it goes off but it's not including a timer. By the time it's been announced it's already too late. I need to know 3-5 seconds before it goes off.\r\n\r\nShadowblaze follows a set timer of:\r\n\r\n0:00 - First bolt\r\n0:30 - 2nd\r\n0:55 - 3rd\r\n1:15 - 4th\r\n1:30 - 5th\r\n1:40\r\n1:50\r\n2:00\r\n2:10 etc.\r\n\r\nBigWigs addon does this but I'm not crazy about BigWigs and would prefer a different timer mod.", "date": "2011-02-01T10:56:24-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "How do you program the in game stopwatch so that it starts at 30sec and then automatically resets and drops 5 sec every interval before making visual and or audio queue that the time has been reached? Or alternatively counts up and sets off an alarm at 30, 55, 1:15, 1:30 etc? I don't believe that's possible without an addon.  I'm not fond of BigWigs but it's much better than the stopwatch. I'm a little busy when add tanking and don't have the time or focus to screw around with a timer that isn't automatic.", "creationdate": "2011-02-04T10:45:31-06:00", "id": 221552, "rating": 7, "commentid": 1318114, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "448060", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Timer to Shadowblaze. Raid lider on first Shadowblaze, press macro, and all raid see timers.  /dbm broadcast timer 00:30 TWO /dbm broadcast timer 00:55 THREE /dbm broadcast timer 01:15 FOUR /dbm broadcast timer 01:30 FIVE /dbm broadcast timer 01:40 SIX /dbm broadcast timer 01:50 SEVEN  You need install DBM to use this macros.", "creationdate": "2011-02-16T16:43:19-06:00", "id": 225692, "rating": 8, "commentid": 1318114, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "terrabit", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "obsolete now, i added this long ago. Including a big special warning 5 second pre warning every time :)", "creationdate": "2011-04-15T17:55:02-05:00", "id": 483666, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1318114, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "mysticalos", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 1336393, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "pthor1234", "body": "Since warlock fear is no longer a viable option to control the adds in phase 1, I (Frost DK) was in charge of kiting them until they de-animate.  What seemed to work best for me, was to do 2 blood strikes on Onyxia right at the start, then swap over to blood presence.  Do this to have 2 blood runes pop up when the adds start coming - it is very helpful.  Then I would have our hunter MD the first add to me, Death and Decay the second add, Outbreak the third add, and howling blast the 4-6th adds.\r\n\r\nYou will eventually get a feel for it, and it can be very effective to let healers aggro some of the skeletons with healing aggro while non-slowed skeletons are running towards you from the MD / DnD / Outbreak, and hit multiple skeletons with Howling blast at once, as well as be able to get some distance.  Once you have 2 or so howling blasts worth of aggro on all skeletons, you can swap to Unholy presence for the additional run speed.\r\n\r\nAt this point, circle around then and group them up as tight as possible, and then right as the first skeleton dies, go in to the pack of them and use hungering cold.  This will freeze them in place long enough for 3 more to die, and it least the last two with 4% and ~12% energy.  Chains of ice root them both, and all the skeletons should die in a nice small clump, making it very easy for your add tank in Phase 3.  If you have a warlock with Shadowfury, get them to pop it on the group right as the first add dies, and you might only have one add left when Hungering cold wears off.\r\n\r\nI made a simple focus macro and hit that when I have the first skeleton targeted, that way I know when he is about to die, so I don't end up leaving a pile of skeletons everywhere.  That made a big difference, since it can be cumbersome to tab through 6 targets to find the lowest energy.", "date": "2011-02-14T18:48:57-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 14, "id": 1344140, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "426853", "body": "As a tank, I find getting initial aggro on Nef himself to be VERY annoying if you're doing it from range.  When I taunt, hit with a judgement, and hit with AS, he still seems to enjoy dropping aggro and switching targets for one melee strike, regardless of whether or not they even touched him (he one-shot one of our add-kiters on multiple occasions).  The only solution I've found to guarantee he [b]WON'T[/b] do this is to make sure you (the tank) are in melee range when he lands, then start backing up.  \r\nNot exactly fun, I'd have much rather been able to avoid having both tanks get hit by a \"buffed\" dragon due to ony/nef proximity, but alas.  You have been warned, it can happen to anybody.", "date": "2011-02-21T00:10:22-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Nobody should be in melee range as he lands anyway, as the centre of the arena is the most dangerous place for getting hit by tail swipes.  Divine Plea to get 3 HP, AW, Judge, chain 1-2 Exocisms depending on time and when he lands smash him with a Shield of the Righteous and he won't be going anywhere :) The other option you have (depending on raid set up) is a Misdirect or Tricks of the Trade for an extra boost - you shouldn't be using these for Onyxia anyway as nobody should really nuking hard until Ony is in place, it's not like P1 is a dps phase anyway.  Good luck!", "creationdate": "2011-02-21T11:31:55-06:00", "id": 479336, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1344140, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Zabuzan1", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "\"the centre of the arena is the most dangerous place for getting hit by tail swipes\" a.k.a. And WATCH tha FOCKING TAIL.", "creationdate": "2012-03-04T12:05:23-06:00", "id": 524654, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1344140, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "MiltiadesBooga", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 15, "id": 1344693, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Zabuzan1", "body": "After getting Nefarian down yesterday for the first time, some tips for general survival!\r\n\r\nDuring phase 1, we had a fire mage and me (ret paladin) kiting the adds. My job was to look after any that spawned in the north whilst the mage took the adds spawning in the south, I repentanced one and turn eviled the other (usually only had 2 to worry about) and after that we chain cc'd them down, kiting them in tight circles when CC broke to ensure they all died on one spot. The mage took the aggro, while I was ready with a Hand of Protection for him, as well as some heals. If I had to HoP him, I immediately applied Righteous Fury and dropped a Consecration and Divine Storm, with taunt ready for any loose adds. While not a conventional kiting combination, it worked very well for our raid group as I am currently threat capped when dpsing so was more useful kiting than auto-attacking Nef or Ony.\r\n\r\nPhase 2 - Anyone with bubble, iceblock, cloak of shadows and so on, save your damage reduction or cancellation spells/techniques for phase 2 if they are on a cool down of greater than 2 mins. Depending on whether or not your group is doing 1 or 2 electrocute during phase 2, either get everyone use the cooldowns at once for 1 electrocute or alternate who is using their cooldown if you have the dps to do a 2nd.\r\n\r\nPhase 1 and 2 are not dps races as such, ensure you will have all your best DPS increasing cooldowns for phase 3.\r\n\r\nFor cooldown use throughout the fight, if you've got a priest aoe bubble on the ground or a paladin's Divine Guardian during an electrocute and you are covered by it, don't waste a personal cooldown, save it for the next electrocute.\r\n\r\nIf you are a dps class with healing spells, remember that a living dps doing lower dps does a lot more damage in a fight than a high dps dieing a preventable death! If you have a warlock get some Healthstones on the go. Paladins have LoH, both for themselves or a fellow raid member in need (try and time it so bubble is available for phase 2 though, usually LoH is only necessary during phase 3 as the damage in P1 is light). Mages can Evocate for health as well as mana. Have a health pot rather than a dps pot. Use bandages - this is best done just before an Electrocute in P1 or P3 as you can get around 5 ticks of a bandage channeled on yourself before any damage interrupts it.\r\n\r\nAll the various methods of healing mean that prior to an Electrocute, everyone should be topped up to the max, even if you have to OOM yourself (as Ret paladins may do with FoL) to survive the Electrocute damage, it's better to be alive and regenerating mana just after than licking the floor.\r\n\r\nAnyway, I had a more structured explanation planned, but my time has been cut short and I've got to go now! I hope some of this may have been beneficial, though tbh it's mostly common sense :)", "date": "2011-02-21T11:26:53-06:00", "rating": 19, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 16, "id": 1350171, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "sanjiyan", "body": "Phase two will have a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=41948]Chromatic Prototype[/url] add spawn onto each of the 3 pillards. They must be interrupted, but to note that they are lvl 85, so you only need +5%hit", "date": "2011-02-25T20:45:33-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 17, "id": 1354825, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "thunderzebra", "body": "In regards to the heroic version of this encounter:\n\n[code]Domination - Phases 1 and 3[/code]\n\n[spell=79318]\n\nDuring phases 1 and 3, random players will get 'dominated' by Nef's 'dominate' and given 2 abilities.\n\n   *the first ability (1, by default) breaks the mind control\n   *[spell=80624], the second ability (2, by default) gives the player a stacking buff up to 150; as you increase your stacks, you gain more stacks per application, so that you get ~30 stacks for one use of Stolen Power by the time you get to 120 stacks. The buff increases damage done by 5% * number of stacks for 18 seconds. [b]150 stacks increases damage done by 750% for 18 seconds.[/b]\n\nWhile dominated, players will move toward a portal, if the player reaches the portal they die instantly. Players may be slowed - earthbind totem, frost trap etc., so that they may stack the buff to higher levels before breaking the mind control.\n\n[b]NOTE 1[/b]: [s]as of this writing, you can use RP walk (default numpad /) before being dominated, resulting in a slow enough movement that you can easily stack the damage buff to 150.[/s] Has been fixed.\n\n[b]NOTE 2[/b]: if you are dominated during an electrocute, you will not take damage.\n\n[b]NOTE 3[/b]: it takes a second or so for the game to register raid-wide buffs (ie - resistance aura) when you release domination; if you release right as an electrocute happens, there is a good chance you will be 1 shot without the resistance.\n\n[b]NOTE 4[/b]: as the ability which breaks mind control will usually be bound to 1, you will want to avoid spamming abilities you normally have bound to 1 while Nef is casting domination.\n\nDue to the enrage timer on Nef, not stacking the buff is not an option. Healers may choose to stack the buff or not, [b]it does increase healing[/b], and, for example, with 150 stacked an efflorescence will full heal everyone standing in it every ~2 ticks.\n\n[code]Explosive Cinders - Phase 2[/code]\n\n[spell=79339]\n\nExplosive Cinders is randomly placed on several players (my only experience is 25 man, in which, iirc, 4 players get the debuff). When this debuff expires, the player will knockback anyone within ~10-12 yards (not certain of the exact range). Due to this, the player(s) with Explosive Cinders must jump off the platform into the lava, far enough way so they won't knock the remaining players on the platform off.\n\n[b]NOTE 1[/b]: when in the lava, do not jump. Every time you jump, you will gain an additional stack of Magma.\n\n[b]NOTE 2[/b]: this is cast several times during phase 2 (not sure of the interval between casts), and may be cast as the lava is residing - you still need to stay away from raid members if you have the debuff when the lava is down.\n\nThe knockback knocks back extremely far. We had people knocked to other platforms.\n\n[code]Additional Notes[/code]\n\n*Walking through fire in p3 while dominated will still cause the fire to grow; cancel MC if you're going to walk through fire.\n\n*The adds in p3 tend to have huge spike damage and, along with electrocute, will often be destroying your kiter. We had 3 (+1 on occasion) out of 7 healers dedicated to focusing on this tank. You will need to use Blessing of Sacrifice/Pain Suppression etc. when adds have recently been rez'd and many are hitting your tank.\n\n*We used a holy paladin with righteous fury to pull adds to the tank. Simply healed and ran slightly ahead of the kiter.\n\n*At current gear levels, you will not be able to push Nef to 70% before phase 2.\n\n*Phase 2 is by far the most difficult phase for healing, so you will not be able to push Nef to 70% (or whatever your next threshold electrocute is, assuming somehow you did get Nef below 70 p1) during this phase.\n\n*More than likely, if you need to use a healthstone, you'll use it phase 2.\n\n*All information was taken strictly from 25 man.\n\n*All raid members should use personal cooldowns for electrocute: Barkskin, Shield Wall, Feint, Raptor Strike (glyph) etc. as much as possible.\n\n*Acquiring [item=62466] for the electrocutes/having to stand in lava with Explosive Cinders is highly recommended. Useful for most end tier bosses.", "date": "2011-03-02T03:42:32-06:00", "rating": 39, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Thank you so much for this! It will cut out those minor tweaks you need before you progress for real.", "creationdate": "2011-03-09T05:59:45-06:00", "id": 480959, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1354825, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "129328", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Really really big Thanks for this info saved like 50~ wipes !", "creationdate": "2011-03-18T13:23:21-05:00", "id": 481716, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1354825, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "K0tY", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-03-13T22:37:02-05:00", 9, "thunderzebra"]}
