{"commentv2": 1, "number": 21, "id": 1366096, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "131617", "body": "Found an odd problem on Nef tonight.  P1 adds were randomly running across the room and aggroing onto the tanks for no apparent reason.  DK and Pally tanks, neither using AoE, single target only on their respective tanking targets.  They don't appear to go for anyone else in the raid who isn't trying to CC them..  Anyone else seen this happening?", "date": "2011-03-13T18:25:54-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Having a similar problem with our first pokes of Neffy with me on my Death Knight Tank (on Onyxia), I believe it is caused by the healing threat created by self healing like Death Strike/Word of Glory then being multiplied by Blood Presence/Righteous Fury. (I deliberately wasn't doing anything with cleaving or AOE)  The solution would be to have a ranged shoot it a bit (with no DOTs) then have them CCed.  They are removing the threat from healing done by Death Strike in 4.1, this maybe one of the reasons.", "creationdate": "2011-03-13T19:14:06-05:00", "id": 232047, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1366096, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "672718", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
