{"commentv2": 1, "number": 24, "id": 1377489, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Mitbrandir", "body": "In ph2 its very handy to get your warlock on the platform where you jump on in the start of the fight. You can easiliy drop your teleport pat on the edge there , and when onxyia dies , walk to the wall at the platform to get in range and instantly keep walking so you jump on the platform , even before there is lava", "date": "2011-03-27T12:12:05-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 25, "id": 1379231, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "lyom", "body": "I have fought many bosses and I must say there is nothing as pleasent to hear as the sound of a male night elf dying to this boss.\r\n\r\nUwwgwgh     AAAAAAAAAAH.", "date": "2011-03-29T13:23:42-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "It helps to think of it not as yelling in death, but yelling in pleasure :D  ....  No, no I don't think that helps. ._.", "creationdate": "2011-04-04T02:47:08-05:00", "id": 482912, "rating": 7, "commentid": 1379231, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Reixes", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Well, that comment is certain to make Nef happy at least, Reixes.", "creationdate": "2012-03-04T12:06:07-06:00", "id": 524655, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1379231, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "MiltiadesBooga", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 26, "id": 1385195, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "652713", "body": "My guild downed him last night. A bit late but we started out late too :P\r\n\r\n\r\nAnyways...\r\nWe ran with a _4_ healer set up (10man normal). We had been wiping on him for about 2-3 full raid nights when we finally decided to try a 4 healer set up since our healers always were running low on mana and couldn't keep up with the immense damage output.\r\n\r\nWe downed him on the first try with that setup.\r\n\r\nIt's strange that I have not seen any tactics suggesting a 4 healer set-up for 10-man.", "date": "2011-04-06T02:49:04-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 27, "id": 1391004, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "Yorgl", "body": "How I manage to jump on the pillar without more than 4 stacks of magma (usually 3, like in the video) : http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PrD_YO2XwIA\r\nSorry for the poor quality... I'm not used to frap fights and upload them on YT. =)\r\n\r\nHope this helps.", "date": "2011-04-14T06:14:25-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "-1", "creationdate": "2011-04-19T11:49:08-05:00", "id": 483882, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1391004, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "lyom", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Well if you find a way to stack less than 3 debuffs (without pal bubble or DK ams etc...) as I do in the vid, I would be glad to see that mate ! ;-) However, so far, I've only seen videos where players explain how to get on the pillar with \"only\" 5 or 6 debuffs. So... Yeah, I assume my method is the most efficient so far.  So, what's so \"-1\" ? ;)  [i]Edit : [/i]This comment was an answer to lyom's comment (which was \"-1\". Just that...) that he deleted meanwhile.", "creationdate": "2011-04-20T02:05:21-05:00", "id": 238713, "rating": 10, "commentid": 1391004, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Yorgl", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Uprated.  I'm linking an instructional video for the new jumpers out there:  [url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y7lF8er_Dv4]6 stacks (with instructions)[/url]  One problem that new jumpers often have is getting too close to the pillar.  Alliance can practice jumping from the SW canals onto boats or docks.  Is there a similar practice spot in a Horde zone or neutral zone?", "creationdate": "2011-08-01T09:02:42-05:00", "id": 255997, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1391004, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "338957", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I only ever got 4-5 stacks, Mage Ward is really nice for blocking lava.", "creationdate": "2011-08-15T01:33:19-05:00", "id": 258661, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1391004, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Skippyninja", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 28, "id": 1392149, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "mysticalos", "body": "something key that is not mentioned about phase 2 mechanic, it has a built in failsafe. From the start of phase 2 to end, nef can only take 15% worth of his health in damage, anything more and he auto pushes, regardless of chromatics or 2 and a half minute auto push (which btw, 3 min i believe applies to 10 man 25 ma seems to be 2:30 on normal, heroic seems to be more like 4 min, it's wierd but there are variations)\n\nSo basically, phase 2 ends if any of following happen.\n\n1. Nef takes 15% damage\n2. All 3 chromatics die on normal\n3. ANY of the chromatics die on heroic\n4. after set time (variable based on difficulty/size)\n\nThis is very important when doing the achievement in meta. It means that for him to actually go below 50% before phase 2 ends, he has to be below 65% when phase 2 starts. Since pushing him below 70% auto explodes onyxia 5 seconds later. the ideal strat is to push him below 70%, then, kill onyxia within the 5 seconds he's channeling electrocute, make sure she does 1-2 seconds before it goes off, so she doesn't explode, once she dies, phase 1 ends as soon as lava fills room, which means you have until then to get him to < 65%. this is easier then it sounds since he's already probably at 68 or 67 by end of electrocute cast, if you held off ony til last second, you only have another 2-3 percent to burn while he walks from hopefully close to wall, to center of room, then takes a couple seconds to lift off ground and fill room.\nThe achievement itself will turn red, indicating failure, it's WRONG. As long as he was below 65% when phase 2 started, you have not failed. To ensure success however, shoot to push him using number 1 above in my list. That is the way to know for sure you were successful. In other words, if phase 2 ends when he reaches 51% with chromatics up, you failed, because that means he was at 66% when phase 2 started, and 15% auto push ended the phase before achievement completed. If phase 2 ends when he'sa t 49% with chromatics up, you were successful, achievement success. Finish off chromatics AFTER you pushed him 15% of his health and know for sure achievement successful", "date": "2011-04-15T17:59:58-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-10-23T02:28:41-05:00", 1, "mysticalos"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 29, "id": 1397128, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "pend", "body": "Can [spell=31821] be used with [spell=19891] to mitigate [spell=94090] aoe dmg?", "date": "2011-04-22T16:00:00-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "No, as [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=94090]Electrocute[/url] is [b]Nature[/b] damage. [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=20043]Aspect of the wild[/url] and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=41533]Healing totem[/url] can mitigate those damage. :)", "creationdate": "2011-04-23T01:18:57-05:00", "id": 239190, "rating": 8, "commentid": 1397128, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Yorgl", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 30, "id": 1407549, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "823265", "body": "Hi all, did somebody [b]skin Nefarian ?[/b] \nI did it yesterday and [b]drop was 29 Blackened Dragonscale[/b]. (require 550 skin. skill; worgen + knife) So, here is no information about skinning drop of the Nefarian. \nThx for answer ;)", "date": "2011-05-02T17:11:07-05:00", "rating": 20, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yes, I was able to skin Nefarian as well.  As a Night Elf I had two Finkle's Skinners and the Gathering Enchant on a pair of gloves to reach the 550 requirement.  He dropped 11 Blackened Dragonscales.", "creationdate": "2011-05-05T15:49:56-05:00", "id": 242039, "rating": 6, "commentid": 1407549, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ogt777777", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-05-02T18:47:49-05:00", 4, "823265"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 31, "id": 1415433, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "barbeque", "body": "A tip for groups facing problems in P1.\r\n\r\nA hunter with a tenacity pet, glyphed for improved mending and unlimited mis-direct to the pet, is able to take care of all the adds without much problem. Pets can also use cower and other defensive CDs to stay alive when damage spikes toward the end.\r\n\r\nNaturally, a dedicated healer is needed to keep up the pet, but the combination of easy threat and the ability to let all the adds die in the same place (so the tank add doesn't burst a blood vessel in P3) makes hunter pet tanking the most clean solution for P1.\r\n\r\nA hunter using pet tanking should stay on adds while they are up to ensure a constant stream of threat to the pet. Since the threat from MD only lasts for a short while, healer aggro may pull off some adds just as they are about to \"die\".\r\n\r\nNaturally, the hunter should also dismiss the tenacity pet and summon a DPS one quickly as soon as the adds \"die\".", "date": "2011-05-10T23:04:02-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-05-17T19:51:13-05:00", 1, "barbeque"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 32, "id": 1425350, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Fulgorater", "body": "[b]For tanks having trouble kiting in P3[/b]\nMy guild kept progressing flawlessly into P3.\n\nWe tanked [npc=41376] in the middle facing the 10 o'clock position, as the adds from P1 were placed in the 12 o'clock position.  Both tanks progressed clockwise to minimize fire exposure and maximize kiting room.\n\nHowever the timing of the fire to the adds were an issue, and the tank had trouble pulling them at the right moment.\n\nWe got a suggestion from a friend to [b]use BigWigs instead of DBM[/b].  As soon as we switched add-ons, we killed him.  The timers and the \"more visible\" effect was clutch.  Hands down now the guild favorite Raiding Add-on.", "date": "2011-05-23T10:02:05-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-05-23T10:02:49-05:00", 1, "Fulgorater"]}
