{"commentv2": 1, "number": 43, "id": 1502918, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "GeneralK", "body": "Nefarian 10m or Nerf-arian as they now call him, is super easy.\r\n\r\nThe fight focuses around 3 phases.\r\n\r\nThe object is to burn Onyxia to 25% then switch to nef while only the Onyxia tank is attacking Ony, going through 2 crackles. Each crackle occurs at 10% past Nef's hp and does approx 60-70k raidwide aoe dmg. Tanks dps and healers should make sure they are topped up before pushing one. or be ready to use a survival Cooldown.\r\n\r\nPhase1. have the kiter pickup adds and run them away from nef/onyxia ( a frost DK is preferred because he can blast adds from afar and spec into chillblains for the fight so he never gets hit, being hit by an add will increase its dmg by 100% making you very likely to die. as a Dk kiter you will probly get zapp'd by onxia once or twice. be sure to pop AMS before that occurs and glyph it for 7 seconds. adds fall over in around 30 seconds so go back to ony after that.\r\n\r\nBurn Onyxia and ignore nef for the most part. Onyxia should be in the farthest right side of the room past the right pillar, and Nef on the far left one. This prevents the 2 dragons from enraging and killing everyone. The only concern with Phase1 for dps/healers should be staying clear of Onyxia's lighting attacks, this is the Onyxia tanks job. turn ony when she starts sparkling then turn her back. when in doubt, stay behind Onyxia, its far better than being zapped continously.\r\n\r\nPhase2. burn the add and interrupt it from casting blast nova, You must have 1 solid 10 second interrupter on each platform and atleast 1 healer on each as well. swimming across the lava may be done but its a very bad idea.\r\n\r\nPhase3: the Add tank will need to kite the bone warrior adds around as Nef is faced in a single direction. just tank n spank mainly till nef's dead. BL whenever u feel comfortable and be sure to survive every crackle.\r\n\r\nnef has been severly nerfed but can still pose problems for pugs. the main key is just to focus on certain elements.\r\np1. proper onyxia positioning, purely the tanks job (as long as the dps didnt pull aggro at the start)\r\n\r\np2 making sure everyone moved to the correct platform\r\n\r\np3 ensuring the adds are kited around in a good pattern without being breathed on.\r\n\r\nfollowing this will ensure victory.\r\n\r\nenjoy.", "date": "2011-08-25T04:37:59-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
