{"commentv2": 1, "number": 52, "id": 1979569, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Caglock", "body": "Soloed 10N as a 550 Destruction Warlock, but since no solo guides are posted I will do it for all classes. If you have a pet tank then this fight is really easy, if not then you need to be either really hard to kill, have really high DPS to kill Nefarian before the [npc=41918] become problematic, or duo with a tank. Tanks can get a lot of vengeance here, so it might be worthwhile to swap to a tank spec if you have one. Warlocks and Hunters shine here, Warlocks can facetank the bone warriors and Hunters can kite them. Guardian Druids also look to be good enough due to [spell=106737]. If you have any form of remote taunt, then nothing else can threaten you. The better gear you have the easier it gets. Better gear lets you burn Onyxia faster, tank bone warriors longer, and/or kill Nefarian faster before the bone warriors become a threat due to [spell=79330].\n\nWhen you jump down to fight Onyxia, if you have a pet then [b]DO NOT[/b] land on the three platforms, the fight starts and your pet is stuck there. Anyway, she should die fast from your opener if you're a DPS, I can't comment for tanks because she died before any major mechanics happened. If you're ranged, as she dies, stand in between two platforms (think about the sides of a triangle), don't worry about the lava. Start shooting one of the three [npc=41948]s, and interrupt the other immediately as [spell=80735] is casted. Make your way to a platform, any platform, once the nova is interrupted. Phase 3 will start as soon as you kill one, and the lava will disappear, but the two other adds are still alive. Kill those, you don't need any more headache in the hardest part of the fight.\n\nPhase 3 is where it gets difficult. The [npc=41918]s hit for ~30k, which doesn't sound bad until you consider that there are several of them, and they eventually become untankable due to [spell=79330]. As to why pet tanking is so good here? [spell=77826] and [spell=81031] refreshes and reanimates the bone warriors, so if you can get a pet to face Nefarian away and move the bone warriors away from the fire, they die, good job. They will eventually get reanimated, it's not the end of the world, just repeat the process. He's not all that remarkable after that, dragon rules (stay to his side, not front or back) still applies, like it has always been for almost 10 years. He doesn't seem to hit particularly hard against my Voidwalker, and his health isn't exceptionally high, so killing him isn't too problematic if you can deal with the warriors.\n\nHaven't had any success 10H though, I die too fast to run into MCs but it seems like it's really hard not because of impossible raid mechanics (Chimaeron), but because they just hit too hard for a 559 clothie to handle.\n\nEDIT: 564 now, and even when duoing with a 523 Prot Warr we still can't kill him 10H. The bone warriors just hit for such a ridiculous amount, and if even one breath or spark hits them before they go down, might as well throw yourself into the lava. It's doable, just not worth the immense effort required. One advice I can give for those who try, however, is to burn defensive CDs in phase 2. It [i]really[/i] hurts compared to normal mode, and it's where a lot of our wipes happened.\n\nEDIT 2: I haven't soloed it since 6.0 but I would imagine that it would be easy now. The adds would get AoE'd down super fast, and even if they get ignited back up then they will still die fast. Mind controls won't be a problem when you can easily pull over 1 million DPS on burst classes, neither will any of the mechanics. Lava phase may still hurt. Note that this entire edit is speculation, the newer comments are far more helpful now.", "date": "2014-07-11T02:26:52-05:00", "rating": 11, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Ya too bad ony doesn't die and sit at 1 HP before killing you", "creationdate": "2014-10-14T23:19:11-05:00", "id": 778683, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1979569, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Furydeath", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2015-01-21T20:23:36-06:00", 9, "Caglock"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 53, "id": 2015102, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "DavivMcD", "body": "Soloed 10 heroic as a 491 Blood DK. It was a pretty close shave, but there are some things I learned to help avoid as much damage as possible:\n\n[ul]\n[li]Get out of the lava as fast as possible, and stay out. It does way more relative damage in 6.0.2 than before. It feels far too strong and is probably an oversight in the stat squish changes, keeping it at 'big stat' damage numbers.[/li]\n[li]KILL ALL 3 CHROMATIC PROTOTYPES. As big and bad Nefarian and the skeleton adds can look in phase 3, they will not do nearly as much damage to you as the constant barrage of Blast Nova, if you let it continue.[/li]\n[li]The biggest single hit you can take in this fight is from Electrocute, which occurs at each and every 10% of Nefarian's health. This means you can control it. The faster you try to burn Nefarian down, the faster you will take damage. If you can't keep up with it, back off of Nefarian and play with the skeleton adds for a while, until your health is back to safe levels or you get a defensive cooldown available again.[/li]\n[li]Don't stand in the purple fire. Duh[/li]\n[/ul]", "date": "2014-10-18T07:40:46-05:00", "rating": 12, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I appreciate this, but it could use a clarification. You say stay out of lava and also kill prototypes... which is it? You can't do both, as you have to go into the lava to get to their platforms and kill them (unless I am missing something). 520 Blood DK, and I breeze through everything until the platforms come up, at which point I either die to Blast Nova or die to the lava.", "creationdate": "2014-10-26T11:19:16-05:00", "id": 782440, "rating": 4, "commentid": 2015102, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "MelTorefas", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Sweet, I went from \"WTF am I doing wrong,\" to reading this, then go back and no troubles at all. Like Daviv said, kill the Cromatic Prototypes. To do this, when the lava comes up, get to a platform, quick. Kill the prototype there. Next, Wait for the lava to go back down (horrible damage from that) while healing if possible. Once that is done, run platform to platform, using ranged attacks to kill the prototypes. Whether it is your ranged holy spells for a ret paladin, or throws for rogues and warriors. Burn them down, and the rest is easy, if you are competent at raiding.", "creationdate": "2014-11-04T12:35:08-06:00", "id": 785872, "rating": 4, "commentid": 2015102, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Canunja", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just to point out on the lava: All lava in the game now does something like 9% of your max health per tick. Doesn't matter where, what level, etc. Lava was always dangerous like this at level, but as you out-leveled a place, the damage became trivial. Now, it's dangerous at any level. It's not the stat squish per se, just a new game mechanic that came out at the same time.", "creationdate": "2015-01-26T05:05:49-06:00", "id": 832773, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2015102, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "fosley", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-10-18T07:41:30-05:00", 1, "DavivMcD"]}
