{"commentv2": 1, "number": 55, "id": 2017974, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "mjmill4", "body": "Dropped as a Prot warr in 551 SMF gear w/a 489 shield.  Used ER, LS, and a lot of SB to keep health up, can't HL or charge the little guys on the platforms, so keep your HP pool up as much as possible.  Other than that, simple fight, 2 min 25 sec.", "date": "2014-10-23T10:09:54-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-10-23T10:10:12-05:00", 1, "mjmill4"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 56, "id": 2021059, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "nubbers", "body": "Soloing this on 10H as Destro was a little challenging at first because I couldn't just burn the boss down in time like most fights. \r\n\r\nI use the Soul Leech talent and Glyph of Healthstone. Just slowly dps'd down Ony and saved embers. Once in phase 3 I summoned my void walker to tank the adds and my doomguard to help burn the boss down. A couple adds hit me but was a cake walk.\r\n\r\n550 ilevel full pvp gear", "date": "2014-10-30T10:51:24-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 57, "id": 2024257, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Marfol", "body": "As a guardian druid still very doable ... In the phase when lava comes up, kill the platform adds and heal yourself afterwards with healing touch and rejuvanation... 532 guardian.", "date": "2014-11-04T09:08:40-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 58, "id": 2025510, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "1394258", "body": "I want to preface this with the fact that I was not playing when the Cata raids were current and have never done this particular raid before. Also, I am a 550 Fury War.\r\n\r\nThis fight was tough! Especially considering the lack of healing output the Fury Warrior has to offer. Honestly, none of these comments helped me much at all! I hope those that are soloing this in 6.02 can gleam some wisdom off of this post!\r\n\r\nUsing the strategies that have been posted, I ended up wiping a good 5-6 times. The lava was too much and heroic leap was not useable. I could never get to a second platform to even attempt to kill any other mobs. On another run, I noticed that if I continued to stay on the first platform and use my ranged(what little range I have!) on Nef, then the lava would start to drop. But I took too much damage from the mobs on the platforms for this observation to do me any good. I decided to try and do things without advancing to phase 2. And it worked!\r\n\r\nI killed Nef in phase 1. \r\n\r\nIt appeared that if I killed Ony, that's what triggered phase 2 eventually. However, I simply brought her down to ~15% and Nefarious came down to the platform. I was able to then kill him by single target focusing him down.\r\n\r\nDie by the Sword helped tremendously while I had Ony, Nef, and the spawned mobs wailing on me. \r\n\r\nMy advice, if you can manage it, is to not kill Onyxia on phase 1, and simply take her down enough so that Nefarious comes down and then you can roflstomp him. Good luck, heroes!", "date": "2014-11-06T19:54:32-06:00", "rating": 44, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This is good advice, which I was coming here to post myself. I'll add that you don't actually have to put any damage into Onyxia at all. If you just wait there, Nefarian will come down naturally after not much time at all. As a prot warrior, I actually had to stop using revenge. That alone was enough to take Onyxia down to 1hp before Nefarian died.", "creationdate": "2014-11-08T14:11:00-06:00", "id": 787251, "rating": 7, "commentid": 2025510, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Virsaevio", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Thank you very much, I managed some form of this after reading your post and dying a couple or more times previously.", "creationdate": "2016-07-06T13:10:39-05:00", "id": 950408, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2025510, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Sereilbex", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 59, "id": 2026673, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "AikaRed", "body": "Solo'd heroic 25 as a 581 prot paladin. I got nefarian to come down by damaging onyxia a little bit, then I focused nefarian  to get as much damage as possible on him before phase change. The aoe damage from the adds werent a problem for me, i only killed one during the lava rise. Move him out of the purple fire and keep holy wrath on cooldown to minimize as much damage as possible from the undead minions. Buffs used were str flask, seal of insight, kings, drums, and str potion. It should be possible to do it with lower gear levels.", "date": "2014-11-08T23:15:47-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-11-10T04:27:22-06:00", 1, "AikaRed"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 60, "id": 2085106, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Angelhearth", "body": "25-man HC Suprisingly easy to solo.\r\n\r\n100 Frost DK (648) in Blood Presence\r\n\r\nI was about to skip it on my way through BWD, but I gave it a shot.\r\n\r\n1. Burn down Onyxia\r\n2. At the end of her life stand near a pillar and burn down the adds\r\n3. On pillar kill add (shouldn't it be one on each of the 3 pillars)?\r\n4. When lava disapears engage Nefarian and burn him down. Use some AoE's on the adds, but it doesn't realy matter.", "date": "2015-01-08T20:06:05-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 61, "id": 2094970, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "fosley", "body": "Just did 25H as a 630 demo lock. The rest of the instance was a joke, even with severe lag. This fight was much harder. The adds were by far the biggest issue, because they have a buff that keeps stacking. At one point they were doing like 5000% of base damage because I was focusing the boss.\n\nTo beat this:\n1. I started by burning Onyxia down (but no cds, just burn her), then the first set of adds disappear (no need to hurt them).\n2. Get some damage on Nefarian while you can until the lava rises. Be near a pillar before the lava so you can get out quickly.\n3. Get on the pillar quickly, then blow up the add on the pillar if you want.* Try to get some healing in during this part.\n4. Once the lava goes down, get off the pillar or the adds will destroy you with throwing knives or something.\n5. Get some damage on Nefarian while you can, building up fury (or whatever resource your class uses). Put some dots on the other pillar adds if you want. Try to be at full health before the adds come out.\n6. When all the adds come out, blow every aoe cd you have and focus them. Don't even worry about Nefarian, just blow the adds to hell as fast as possible. Use any kind of defensives or healthstones/pots during this phase. Edit: Tried it again this week, and I found that using the Wrathguard with Threatening Presence turned on really helps this phase.\n7. Move out of purple, but quickly return to killing adds.\n8. Once the adds are done, Nefarian is a joke. Murder him with fire. Or ice, or steel, or whatever you have handy.\n\n[small]*I jumped onto the first pillar to start the fight and left a demonic circle up. When the lava came up, I climbed onto one of the other pillars and killed that add. While the lava was still up, I demon leaped towards the first pillar so I was in range, then teleported to it and killed that add. This way I had two adds down without being in the lava much, but you're probably fine with none of them dead.[/small]", "date": "2015-01-26T05:30:24-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2015-02-02T18:21:57-06:00", 1, "fosley"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 62, "id": 2098187, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "createdbyx", "body": "Fairly easy on 25man heroic solo Feral Druid 642 iLevel at level 100.\r\n\r\nBut you can still take a good amount of damage if you spend too much time in the lava.\r\n\r\nHere is a video [url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s3TV_-uPTeQ]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s3TV_-uPTeQ[/url]", "date": "2015-02-02T03:31:16-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 63, "id": 2133681, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "xunce", "body": "Protip for the Hunters out there; If you tame Chimaeron, you will be unable to engage Nefarian, as the orb will only spawn after all bosses have been [i]registered[/i] as dead. Your taming of Chimaeron doesn't classify him as killed, so you're SOL if you want to tame him and clear the entire instance. One or the other.", "date": "2015-03-09T19:48:36-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 64, "id": 2146068, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "romansamurai", "body": "Killed him on Heroic 25m as 670 combat rogue.  Leeching poison is your friend to survive all the adds.  Don't even bother hitting Onyxia, if you wait long enough he'll come down.  But you can dps the adds for the leeching poison to heal you.\r\n\r\nOnce he comes down, just DPS him down.  Leeching poison should keep you healed enough to survive adds damage no problem.  Turn on blade flurry around 30% if you want and get rid of some adds, but up to you.  Can DPS him down without touching adds or Onyxia and survive the damage thanks to Leeching Poison.\r\n\r\nGood luck!", "date": "2015-03-28T21:11:36-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 65, "id": 2161373, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "cujo832000", "body": "soloed 25 H 662 (mixed gear ) prot pally stayed on the bosses ignored the adds got out of lava as fast as i could  thats all it was way easier than other boss fights in this raid", "date": "2015-04-11T18:35:01-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 66, "id": 2163744, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "endersblade", "body": "Just cleared this on 25H with a 609 ilevel Destro Warlock.  I was using Soul Leech for talent, and it is a godsend.  The minions beat on me to no avail.\r\n\r\nI used the strat of beating on Ony until Nef comes down.  Then just focus fire on him.  Eventually for some reason Ony died (not sure if scripted or my VW did something), the minions actually die off one at a time after a while too.  Once lava came up, I took out just one of the guys on the pillars then went back to focusing on Nef, eventually the lava went back down and just repeated until he was dead.  Maloriak gave me a MUCH harder time than this did, but this fight just takes forever.", "date": "2015-04-14T23:35:57-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 67, "id": 2164967, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "multiversekyle", "body": "Took me a little while to get it down but just soloed this as a lvl100 BM Hunter. The key is to concentrate on Nefarian and leave Onyxia alone. I put my pet on passive (spirit beast for the heals), jumped down, and just blasted Nefarian. I ignored the mobs that spawn and Onyxia and just kept on Nefarian.\n\nIf you don't damage Onyxia, the lava never comes and everything else is actually not all that bad. The first several times, I burned Onyxia down and was killed pretty quickly. One time my pet killed Onyxia while I was blasting Nef so the next time I put him on passive and was able to finish.", "date": "2015-04-16T21:34:04-05:00", "rating": 31, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "One could just burn ony to get the lava up and the adds to despawn, then while on the platforms burn nef while he's hovering (if you are range) and just before he dies the lava will recede and you can drop down and finish him off. Though sometimes just killing the first add on the pillar will cause the lava to drop so you don't have to kill the other two.", "creationdate": "2016-04-14T23:28:07-05:00", "id": 938280, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2164967, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "KenjiT28", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I took Ony down to 20% or so and Nef didn't come down at all. All those trash mobs started doing some serious damage. How are you guys even avoiding the trash damage? It adds up so quickly and there are so many of them. Nef came down once Onyx was at 0% - but it could be a timed thing. At least I got a breather when the lava started rising, I moved on to the platforms and blasted Nef to death. I was a mage with 4% leech and ilevel 676. Without the leech I would have died 10 times over.", "creationdate": "2017-02-10T03:03:31-06:00", "id": 1031599, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2164967, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "huldu", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2015-04-16T21:35:23-05:00", 1, "multiversekyle"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 68, "id": 2224469, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "cephadex", "body": "[u]In order to start the fight with Nefarian:[/u]\r\n\r\nYou must first kill all the other bosses in Blackwing Descent. \r\n\r\nThen, to activate the encounter, activate (click on) the orb with green swirly lights located outside Atramedes' chamber.", "date": "2015-08-03T07:51:58-05:00", "rating": 81, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
