{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 1254839, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "intuit", "body": "This is the mob/thing/whatever that casts Electrocute (105k raid-wide aoe) during the Nefarian encounter in Blackwing Descent.  It is a spell that is cast on the entire raid each time you drop Nefarian 10%.  At  X9.9%, you will see an emote for it and the aoe will hit 5seconds later.\n\nFor some reason, during 25man only, the first time this is about to happen I start getting really bad and strange lag and it continues randomly throughout the fight.  It's not like normal fps lag, as it also kind of makes my game make a slight popping noise each time the frames skip.  Almost seems like it's an external application starting up and taking a HUGE amount of my computer's resourses.  Very odd, and it wasn't just me that had this occuring to them during our raid.  Maybe Blizz is working on a fix.", "date": "2010-12-23T13:34:12-06:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-12-23T13:35:08-06:00", 1, "intuit"]}
